  "source_dataset": "county_sheriffs",
  "note": "All 66 South Dakota counties have their own elected sheriff and none contract the office out; the two reservation/seat-less counties keep their own sheriffs (Oglala Lakota's Vanessa Plume works from Hot Springs in Fall River County, which supplies its jail/administrative services, while primary reservation policing is by the Oglala Sioux Tribe DPS/BIA; Todd County's Robert Sedlmajer likewise coexists with Rosebud Sioux tribal/BIA police), and even tiny Buffalo County retains its own sheriff; sheriffs currently in office were elected in 2022 (terms run through Jan. 2027), so 2026 election winners such as Minnehaha's Josh Phillips take office Jan. 2027 except where sworn in early (e.g., Hughes County's Jeff Metzinger, installed June 2026)."
